This paper deals with wireless network topologies and their routing, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of geometric properties of the connectivity graph, which suggests a possible connection to data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper proposes a low-overhead scheme, which could be related to machine learning (cs.LG) or signal processing (cs.SI) techniques.
